Six underground designers redefining streetwear to follow
Six underground designers redefining streetwear to follow Published on 21 March 2018 Text Emma Firth Share 
N ineties-inspired athleisure has been in fashion’s frame for some time now. But what’s next? From emerging brands such as 032c taking inspiration from Berlin’s techno scene to elevated utilitarian styles pushing the boundaries of technical sportswear, here’s Hunger ’s pick of the lesser-known labels putting their own avant-garde spin on streetwear…